    "causal_summary": "The shared skill-advisor scorer — the weighted five-lane fusion that ranks which skill a prompt should route to — carries a saturation-class defect: explicit-lane disambiguation penalties are pre-clamp additive offsets and the fusion floors net-negative lane matches to zero, so durable negative evidence is erased the moment saturating positive support reappears",
